Polycystic ovary syndrome, or #PCOS, is a condition characterized by hyperandrogenism and chronic anovulation
#PCOS is an enigma, in that it is a heterogeneous disorder, with the severity of clinical #hyperandrogenism
The appearance of polycystic-appearing ovaries (multiple tiny cysts) on ultrasonography is noted in as many as 20% of women who have #PCOS
its original description in the medical literature in the 1800s, #PCOS was called cystic oophoritis.
In 1930s Stein and Leventhal first diagnosed what was initially coined Stein-Leventhal syndrome, known now as #PCOS
#PCOS currently is viewed more as a metabolic disorder, with an array of cardiac and metabolic risk factors.
Studies have shown....more than 75% of hirsute women have #PCOS.
